    <article class="bl-article">

      <p class="bl-intro speakable">Graeagle golf season runs from May through October — six months at 3,500–5,000 feet elevation in the Sierra Nevada. The courses don't open until snowmelt clears the fairways, and they close when the first hard freeze arrives in fall. Within that window, the month you choose matters more than most golfers realize.</p>

      <h2>The Short Answer</h2>
      <p>Most Graeagle courses open in <strong>early to mid-May</strong>. The season peaks through summer, hits its most enjoyable stretch in <strong>September and October</strong>, and closes by early November. The best combination of conditions, availability, and price is September — not July.</p>

