      <h2>What "Elevation Golf" Means for Conditions</h2>
      <p>Graeagle's five courses sit between 3,500 and 5,000 feet. At this elevation:</p>
      <ul class="bl-list">
        <li><strong>The ball flies 6–8% farther.</strong> Your 150-yard 7-iron becomes a 160-yard carry. Adjust every club selection.</li>
        <li><strong>Mornings are cold even in July.</strong> Tee times before 8am in early June can mean frost delays or cart restrictions. Book the 9am–11am window for the best conditions.</li>
        <li><strong>Afternoon thunderstorms are possible in July–August</strong>, especially at Nakoma Dragon and Grizzly Ranch, which sit higher on ridgelines. Check weather morning-of. Most courses will clear you off the course if lightning approaches.</li>
        <li><strong>September–October conditions are exceptional.</strong> Firm fairways, fast greens, cool air, and the aspens turning gold in the Mohawk Valley are reasons experienced Graeagle golfers return every fall.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Morning or Afternoon: When to Tee Off</h2>
      <p>At Graeagle's elevation, the time of your tee time matters as much as the month.</p>
      <ul class="bl-list">
        <li><strong>Morning rounds (7am–10am):</strong> Best in July and August when afternoon storms are possible. Cooler temperatures firm the greens through the morning. At Grizzly Ranch and Nakoma Dragon — both above 4,800 feet — early starts are strongly recommended in peak summer to clear the exposed ridgeline holes before weather builds.</li>
        <li><strong>Midday rounds (10am–1pm):</strong> The sweet spot in May, June, September, and October. By 10am the frost has cleared, fairways are firm, and afternoon weather is rarely a concern in the shoulder months. Best pace of play and most relaxed round.</li>
        <li><strong>Afternoon rounds (1pm+):</strong> Fine in September and October when weather is stable. Avoid at the higher-elevation courses in July–August. Whitehawk Ranch's open meadow layout is more exposed to afternoon wind off the valley than the pine-sheltered layouts at Plumas Pines and Graeagle Meadows.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>When to Book for Each Season</h2>
      <table class="bl-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Month</th><th>Book ahead</th><th>Why</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>May</td><td>1–2 weeks</td><td>Low demand, easy availability</td></tr>
          <tr><td>June</td><td>2–3 weeks</td><td>Season ramping up, weekends fill</td></tr>
          <tr><td>July–Aug</td><td>4–6 weeks</td><td>Peak season — Grizzly Ranch and Nakoma fill fastest</td></tr>
          <tr><td>September</td><td>1–2 weeks</td><td>Demand drops sharply after Labor Day</td></tr>
          <tr><td>October</td><td>Call ahead</td><td>Verify courses are still open — some reduce hours</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Elevation by Course: Why Timing Varies</h2>
      <p>Not all five Graeagle courses are at the same elevation — and that gap determines which opens first in spring and which closes earliest in fall.</p>
      <table class="bl-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Course</th><th>Elevation</th><th>Typically opens</th><th>Typically closes</th><th>Storm risk (Jul–Aug)</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><a href="/portfolio/graeagle-meadows-golf-packages/">Graeagle Meadows</a></td><td>4,400 ft</td><td>Late April–early May</td><td>October–November</td><td>Low</td></tr>
          <tr><td><a href="/portfolio/whitehawk-ranch-golf-packages/">Whitehawk Ranch</a></td><td>4,400 ft</td><td>Early May</td><td>Late October</td><td>Low–moderate</td></tr>
          <tr><td><a href="/portfolio/plumas-pines-golf-packages/">Plumas Pines</a></td><td>4,400 ft</td><td>Early May</td><td>Late October</td><td>Low</td></tr>
          <tr><td><a href="/portfolio/nakoma-dragon-golf-packages/">Nakoma Dragon</a></td><td>4,500 ft</td><td>Mid-May</td><td>Mid-October</td><td>Moderate</td></tr>
          <tr><td><a href="/portfolio/grizzly-ranch-golf-packages/">Grizzly Ranch</a></td><td>4,800–5,400 ft</td><td>Mid-May</td><td>Mid-October</td><td>Highest</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>Grizzly Ranch's 600-foot elevation range across the course means upper holes can have frost while lower holes are already clear. On May opening days, carts may be restricted to paths until the upper fairways fully dry. If you're planning a May trip, call Grizzly Ranch directly to confirm cart access before booking.</p>

      <h2>Which Courses Open First and Close Last?</h2>
      <p><a href="/portfolio/graeagle-meadows-golf-packages/">Graeagle Meadows</a> sits at the lowest elevation in the valley and typically opens first in spring — sometimes late April in warm years. <a href="/portfolio/nakoma-dragon-golf-packages/">Nakoma Dragon</a> and <a href="/portfolio/grizzly-ranch-golf-packages/">Grizzly Ranch</a> sit higher and may open a week or two later if snow is slow to melt. All five courses are generally open by mid-May.</p>
      <p>In fall, the same pattern reverses: Graeagle Meadows tends to stay open latest, sometimes through early November. The higher-elevation courses may close in mid-October if an early storm arrives.</p>

